Name: Benghazi
Description: Benghazi is the second largest city in Libya, with a population of 647.000.

Name: Ghadamis
Description: Ghadamis is an oasis town in Libya. Old part of the town is inscribed on UNESCO World Heritage List.

Name: Sabha
Description: Sabha is the capital of the municipality by the same name in Libya.  It was once the capital of the ancient Fezzan region.

Name: Shahhat
Description: Shahhat (Arabic: شحات) is a town in northeastern Libya, on the Mediterranean coast. It is the birthplace of St. Mark the Evangelist.

Name: Surt
Description: Surt (also Sirt, Sirte) is a city in Libya, best known as Muammar Gaddhafi's hometown. Prior to the civil war of 2011 it was bestowed with a number of governmental edifices subsequently destroyed by NATO aerial bombardment, relentless shelling by NTC rebel forces and then subjected to vandalism and looting of the remains following the killing Muammar Gaddhafi and the suspension of combative activities on 21 October 2011.

Name: Tobruk
Description: Tobruk is a port city in the north-east of Libya.

Name: Zuwara
Description: Zuwara is a port city in northwestern Libya.

Name: Gaberoun
Description: Gaberoun is a small former Bedouin village on a wonderful oasis, around 150 km west of Sabha in the North African country of Libya.

Name: Ghat (Libya)
Description: Ghat is an ancient settlement in Libya.

Name: Leptis Magna
Description: Leptis Magna, also spelled Lepcis Magna, is a UNESCO World Heritage Site on the Mediterranean coast of North Africa in the Tripolitania region of Libya.
